abstract = {Security and reliability are of vital importance for a remote system to facilitate effective monitoring and management of a wide range of equipment. A distributed secure monitoring system based on blockchain and IoT technologies is proposed in the paper. Firstly, a lightweight security scheme (LSS) is proposed to provide a high level of security with reduced computational and communication costs. Secondly, the architecture of remote monitoring system is presented. An identity authentication method based on the LSS is proposed to authenticate any new node when joining the network. A secure access control method based on blockchain is also proposed to increase the security of the system in a lightweight and scalable manner. Finally, the proposed monitoring system is analyzed with regard to the security against several well-known attacks.},
